        2nd May 2025

        Vote score

        i've realised that one of the reasons for the recent drought of good hits is that all the heavy-hitter artists released last year and 2025 has almost been completely reliant on new artists. the dominating artists in 2024 were the likes of billie eilish, beyonce, ariana grande, charli xcx, post malone, hozier, dua lipa, kendrick lamar, bruno mars, etc. all massive household names, and while there were breakthrough artists, many had a lot of momentum and backing from the general public and music industry building up for some time (sabrina, chappell, gracie, shaboozey, teddy swims)

        fast forward to 2025, the dominating artists right now are the likes of alex warren, lola young, ravyn lenae, sombr, doechii, chrystal, benson boone, myles smith, wizthemc, etc. the top 40 is mostly new/upcoming artists and regardless of my dislike for a few of their songs, i have to give props where they're due to the newcomers. the massive influx of a-listers releasing music last year and taking a break this year has led to a massive surge of popularity for new artists but also a weird situation where artists who clearly have a lot of growing room are being catapulted into mega stardom chart-wise.

        its okay if u dont wanna read all that lol
